# Review checklist for packages in unapproved

- bugs mentioned in changelog and sources.changes file
- make sure all mentioned bugs are public
- the upload is a minimal change
- changes file includes previous versions if needed
- fix present in later supported releases
- fix present in devel release
- correct package versioning
- no dependency on another SRU that needs to land at the same time
- New upstream version? Does uscan work?
- if the bug invokes a package-specific procedure, see https://documentation.ubuntu.com/sru/en/latest/reference/package-specific/ for instructions
- ensure no unrelated changes in the diff
- are there NEW packages in debian/control? If yes, this needs a AA/SRU combined review, see https://canonical-ubuntu-project.readthedocs-hosted.com/maintainers/AA/aa-new-review/#new-packages-targeted-at-stable-releases and https://documentation.ubuntu.com/sru/en/latest/explanation/non-standard-processes/#new-queue-in-the-sru-context
- bug has correct ubuntu releases tasks
- SRU template on each referenced bug is properly filled in
- if the bug involves the kernel, make sure that both the GA and HWE kernels are included in the test plan
- the test plan should cover normal usage of the package
- the test plan show a good user story, and not just test the specific change introduced
- update-maintainer was run, if needed
- no changes affecting translations
- if phasing was halted due to errors, the changes should address that: https://ubuntu-archive-team.ubuntu.com/phased-updates.html
